 In particular, we ask about the optimal spacing and seed rate for maize.
 The options are 1) One foot between plants and 2 and ½ foot between rows
 with one seed per hill; 2) One foot between plants and 2 and ½ foot between
 rows with two seeds per hill; and 3) Two foot between plants and 2 and
 ½ foot between rows with two seeds per hill.
 
