\begin_layout Subsection
Impact of treatment on adoption dynamics
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We start by testing the main hypothesis of this paper—that farmers that
 were made aware of the fact that improved seed also need complementary
 inputs—behave differently in terms of seed use in the subsequent season.
 In particular, we look at use of fresh improved seed varieties (our key
 adoption indicator that was also used in Figure 
